item.title: Welcome to dmBizClub
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
About dmBizClub

Hi my name is Rob Darwin and welcome to dmBizClub! I am the founder of Digital Mail, the company behind dmClub. CHANGE. dmClub provides innovative telephony services to small and growing businesses. You probably know us for our virtual numbers of switchboards and you are probably wondering what dmBizClub is all about. When I launched dmClub some 15 years ago we always intended it to have a club atmosphere. To be honest, we struggled to get customers passionate about telecoms but one thing is very clear, everyone is passionate about their business. In a nutshell, dmBizClub is a hub for customers who are passionate about growing their business. I have assembled a small and growing team of leading business growth experts in a number of important areas who will be giving you lots of useful insights to help your businesses flourish. Most important of all, this advice is all free to customers:
  • Free offline events where you can meet and learn from our better business gurus
  • Free online seminars and webinars
  • Free clinics to help you resolve tricky business problems
  • Lots of free articles with concise insights on a specific topics
  • dmBizClub articles where you can share experiences with other members
We also want dmBizClub to be a place where you can network and win more business and a place where you can get special offers on business related products and services. I hope you find this site useful and please do give us your feedback and let us your suggestions for how we can make it better for you. Best wishes

item.title: Recurring payment FAQ
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: FAQ Will you systematically overcharge my account like some utility companies? No, we will not. If we over-estimate how much you need in one month, then there will be less charge I the next month. Can I cancel a Recurring Payment at any time, or am I locked in? The recurring payment is just a way of paying, it is not a contract. You will get an email 10 working days before we take the payment, explaining our calculations, and you can suspend the Direct Debit on the web, Cancel the direct debit, and of course call support if you have any concerns. Obviously if you have a contract with us, this does not give you the option to get out of the contract. Can I change my easy payments, if you send me a proposed easy payment request? Yes, also you do not have to make the easy payment if we suggest it to you.
